annotation.TEXT: The shell-less koopa appeared that time (and then got fried immediately, but he did appear).
First of all, is there stuff to the left? Yep.
I hope my translation was accurate...

No shell-less koopa there? Was I really at the sprite limit? The sprites nearby at the time: The koopa/shell, the springboard, and maybe the goal tape. Just those three as far as I know, but was there something else I wasn't aware of?
Wow, midpoint already? Also, it's a real party over here!

I'll try not to waste too much time in this level, since it's almost entirely the same, but I'm still going to collect all the Yoshi coins (and probably all the loose coins too, but I won't waste time with multi-coin blocks).
So, what's with the pink water? Did that Neapolitan level make the water a resident of Naples?
Well, I hope you all enjoyed watching me play through Hacks 101! But, assuming the world doesn't end on the 21st, I'll probably make a bonus episode. See ya for now!
Yes! Even the cape feather is here! Oh, but why is the screen scrolling up? The original Mondo had no vertical scroll... Well, whatever.
Whoa, hello! Well, that Yoshi coin was obviously placed on a subscreen boundary! (Wouldn't that fit better in Cutoff Canyon Pawprint version 2.5, though?)
I've gotta stop eating those Sloppy Joes...
Yeah, that other level put me in some sort of funky mood, but this level makes my mood more pleasant.
Yeah, I didn't need any more lives anyway. Also, funny spin jump sound effect.
Oh, yeah. Is there anything up this vine?
Oh, and finally... It's time for "Oh, and finally..."! (BTW, you can't advance to the left of "Oh, and finally..." yet. I tried.)
YESSSS!!! ...NOOOOO!!! I got the 50, but I didn't land back on Yoshi...
I hope I can get some power ups early on...
I'll just let those Chucks fall overboard...
I just noticed... This level only gives you 200 seconds. No wonder my time ran low last time. (I didn't think I was dawdling that much...)
A pipe? No, an ambush! Dang it. Why didn't the screen scroll up for me there?
4-life combo! Yay, I still managed to finish this hack with 99 lives!
So, tear your way through the Chucks, and grab the shiny Wiggler head to clear the level! (Also, you should get a hidden 1-up along the way.)
Ahh, much better. A few koopas are still suicidal, but the colors look way better now.
Demo count: 2
Ooh, more funky colors, and unusual music for a cave. Also, LOL at the suicidal koopa!
BURN! BURN! BURN TO THE GROUND! WOO! BURN! TRI-FORMATION! BURN TO THE GROUND! BURN TO THE GROUND! WOO! BURN TO THE GROUND! BURN!
Alright, let's go home.
Alright, so this level seems okay so far...
Okay, now to play this level normally.
That was a cool triple kill!
Octuple gulp!
You can get a fresh Yoshi here if you need one.
Still no 50... I will get at least one 50 before I end this video, or my name's not SomeGuy712x!
I guess I'll hit this goal point now so I don't have to worry about it later, and then come back and play this level normally.

I think these are mostly in the same language as the last message box in the last level of Chaos CompleXX, in case that helps. Actually, maybe Tails_155 knows what they mean, since he put those messages there...
Wait... Not Awesome! This is Mondo!
Umm... I'm sorry but I just couldn't translate these. Google Translate was of no use whatsoever. Hey, PeejsterM? Maybe you could translate these?
Yep, this is totally Mondo! Just without the water, a different palette, and those starting mushrooms.
Yeah, that can be a problem. However, doesn't the goal's appearance usually cause a different sprite to vanish instead?
Septuple kill! (Maybe one of these days, I should insert Flame Hyenard's actual voice clips for that reference!)
Alright, I can get a flower here, along with a bunch of coins that I don't need.
Whoa, getting a little carried away with your cape, Mario?
This level's basically identical to the previous one, except for the color palette and the timer, which starts at 400 here (and a couple other differences, which I'll point out later).
Uh, no secret exit here this time, but there are two 1-ups and a fire flower.

I wonder why Nintendo made it so that the Dino-Rhino-Hino-Pinos were immune to shell attacks? I mean, you can slide-kill them, and the small ones are flammable and inflammable, so why the shell immunity?
Huh. This isn't custom music, so why isn't this song in "sped-up" mode due to the timer having fallen under 100 seconds here?
Man, why do I tend to get more sloppy while riding Yoshi? Well, at least I've been doing a good job of keeping him from falling off a cliff!

I wonder how many of us have done a blatant Yoshi's Island 1 edit. (I don't know if I have, because I did do this Ctrl+Del thing with the very first level I made, but I think there were a few occasions when I didn't Ctrl+Del first.)
Yeah, something eye-searing or seizure-inducing is not good. However, the particular colors used in this level are kind of cool-looking in a way.
Okay, and yeah, that's everything over there that the side area sends me past.
And of course, that hit occurred after I hit midpoint, so I can't just get a free supersize with my happy meal now.
Bye, Yoshi! At least I didn't let you fall off a cliff or anything!
Okay, and now it's gerbil pal's cleaner counterpart, "Proper Palettes"! (Sponsored in part by the big N.)
What? The yellow blocks are actually ice blocks? I did not know that! Well, that should allow me to get my lost life back easily!
Okay, so the yellowish coins here are worth 1, the blue-greenish ones are worth 2, and the pinkish ones with the yellowish outlines are worth 5. Got it.
Spring! Actually, that's not for another three months, as Winter is just about to officially start.
Okay, let's try to clear out some of these guys to reduce slowdown.
Whoa! It's a Chuck-apalooza! Good thing I've got a cape!
Quadruple gulp! Good thing I've got Yoshi!
Hello, and welcome to the finale of Hacks 101! Yes, I'm going to finish all of the remaining levels today, beginning with "Sprit Overload and some white-colored pieces of a smashing pillar".
Well, let's quickly get this bonus game over with.
Now, for some reason, it's the green blocks that are the normal spinny turn blocks, and the yellow blocks are just completely solid.
That was an interesting way to hit the multi-coin block.
Also, "Palits"? Maybe it's a pal of some kind?
Whoooaaa... I think I had too many mushrooms, bro... Check out them funky colors, yo...
Ah, and even this world gets a color change (for instance, the now pink WNTD letters). However, you have to leave and return to this map after clearing "Oh, and finally..." to see this.
Found the secret exit, but I'll come back for that later.
Awesome!

Translation: "Don't talk to players about how cool you are in text boxes. If they think you're cool after they play, that's cool, but let them decide that. Or else, you'll sound egotistical. Pawprint."
Okay, I'd better stop fooling around.
Oh, that's right. Since I completed the special world, the overworld color palette changes. I guess I'll show off all of the maps with the new colors.
And with this 1-up, I am now at 99 lives! So, as long as I don't die in some silly way, that's what I'll finish with!
I take it there's no way to reach that sunken ship over there?
Also, other things, like the old BlockTool, can exasperate the slowdown problem as well, so be aware of that.
Make sure Chuck is exterminated completely...
Okay, so have I taken out everybody in this direction yet?
Whoa, that's weird how that path got revealed, but whatever. I'm not heading that way yet. First I need to quickly go back for the secret exit in this level!
Now, this side area appears to be totally unaltered. I'd fast-forward through it, but it's not very long.
Whoa, Mario almost took off on me there. That almost tossed me into the abyss!
Whoa, that was weird. One of the times Yoshi was hit there didn't cause him to flee. I think it's because I pressed A at that exact instant.
Hextuple gulp!
Whoops, I missed a Chuck, but that's okay. It's not like he can kill me now-- WHAT THE?!?!?!?
That was a cool unlock!
Huh. That row of ? blocks wasn't there in the other version of this level...
Chuck just Kaizo trapped me!
And that's everything over-- Whoa! There I go, getting sloppy again. Better make this landing carefully...
No Yoshis because they're allergic to finales.
I fail at failing...
Wait, I'm not going to somehow slip through that spinning block, right? Nope, I'm safe. Good.
Oh, I am so going to get revenge... First, let me step into the gerbil level for a moment and use my reserve power up...
Okay, I really gotta clear out these guys...
Argh! More sloppiness! But, at least it's the non-fatal kind.
"Terble"? Is that some sort of new breed of gerbil?
But, yeah, you should probably stick to more eye-pleasing palettes in general.
Yep, this definitely could qualify as eye-searing. Okay, let's see if I can figure these coins out...
So, can I maybe get 50 this time?
Okay, now for this coolzorz-sounding level!
Oh, good, and here's the end of the level. Well, that was kind of fun, in a way.
10-life combo! Well, Tails_155, you said you wanted me to finish this hack with 99 lives, and it's looking very likely now!
Ooh, good thing I didn't collect that enemy coin at first. I need the koopa shell in order to safely open that 1-up block, since there's no water.

Man, we've got all of the football teams partying here for some reason. The New England Patriots... the New York Giants... The Gensokyo Onis... Name a football team (real or just-made-up-on-the-spot), and it's probably in this level!
Alright, Chucks, you are toast!!!
Note: Your mileage may vary on that.
Huh. Well, that's interesting. If you jump here at just the right angle and hold right, this can happen. (Probably requires Yoshi and maybe a cape too.)
Oh, yeah, I just gotta point out that the land formations look really cool here!
Bye, koopa!
Oh, these are new too.
Ooh, that 1-up was green-flavored!
Also, I'll just go and speed through this bonus game here...
Okay, I think I've gotten over those funky mushrooms. This color palette looks a lot more fitting.
Looks like it, except for those clowns off screen, which I'm not going to bother with since I can't see anything up there.
